                <div class="mt-6">
                  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Profile</h2>
          
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">
                      <strong>Professor Prem Lal Patel</strong>, Director of VNIT, Nagpur, took over the additional charge as Director of <strong>IIIT Nagpur</strong> on <strong>1st October 2024</strong>. He is a <strong>Professor (HAG) of Hydraulics and Water Resources</strong> in the Department of Civil Engineering at <strong>Sardar Vallabhbhai National Institute of Technology (SVNIT), Surat</strong>.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">
                      He served as <strong>Deputy Director</strong> of SVNIT from <strong>September 17, 2019, to September 16, 2022</strong>, and has held various key positions such as <strong>Dean (PG), Dean (R&C), Dean (Academic), and Head of Civil Engineering Department</strong> at SVNIT Surat.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">
                      Prior to joining SVNIT in 2007, he was an <strong>Associate Professor</strong> at <strong>Delhi College of Engineering (now DTU)</strong> for eight years. Before that, he worked as an <strong>Assistant Executive Engineer (Civil)</strong> in the <strong>Border Roads Organization (BRO), Ministry of Road Transport and Highways, Government of India</strong> from <strong>1995 to 1999</strong>.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">
                      He completed his <strong>Bachelor’s in Civil Engineering</strong> from <strong>Government Engineering College, Rewa, Madhya Pradesh</strong>, and later pursued his <strong>Master’s and Doctoral degrees</strong> from <strong>Indian Institute of Technology Roorkee</strong> (formerly University of Roorkee).
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">
                      His research expertise includes <strong>River Mechanics and Flood Control</strong>, <strong>Hydrological Modeling</strong>, and the <strong>Impact of Climate Change on Water Resources</strong>. He has guided <strong>14 Doctoral theses</strong>, <strong>49 Master’s theses</strong>, and has executed <strong>6+ high-value sponsored research projects</strong> and <strong>25+ consultancy projects</strong>. His work has been widely recognized, with <strong>260+ research papers</strong> published in reputed journals and conferences.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">
                      Prof. Patel has represented India at several international research forums and has visited countries like the <strong>United States, Netherlands, China, Italy, Japan, and Dubai</strong> to present his research.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">
                      He was previously part of the <strong>Climate Change Working Group of IAHR</strong> dealing with <strong>Fluvial Mechanism</strong>. He is a <strong>Fellow Member</strong> of the <strong>Indian Society for Hydraulics, Indian Water Resources Society, and Institution of Civil Engineers, India</strong>. He played a key role in establishing a <strong>Centre of Excellence (CoE) on Water Resources & Flood Management</strong> at SVNIT Surat, funded by the <strong>World Bank-sponsored TEQIP-II</strong>.
                  </p>
              
    
